13/02/2007
BRUSSELS, Belgium -- Foreign ministers of the EU-Western Balkans Forum held their regular meeting in Brussels on Monday (February 12th), focusing on progress in EU- related reforms and criteria for Stabilisation and Association Agreements.
They also discussed regional co-operation and latest developments in the region, including UN envoy Martti Ahtisaari's status plan for Kosovo.
Macedonian Foreign Minister Antonio Milososki, meanwhile, met with EU Commissioner for Regional Policy Danuta Huebner.
She stressed that power decentralisation and efficient local administrative capacity would be very important to Macedonia's EU integration bid.
(Dnevni Avaz - 13/02/07;
MIA, Makfax, MRT, HINA, RTRS - 12/02/07)
